Material shaders
----------------

In older games, a single image qualified as a texture and all that was required was that you simply drop the corresponding image into a specific folder. The general concept in the [Id\_Tech\_4.html id Tech 4] family is to use [Material\_(decl).html material shaders] which in turn use multiple [Images.html images], each representing a different property of a surface. This makes texturing more work than it was in the past, but it also gives much more power and flexibility to the developers.

Check the following links to learn more about the syntax of material files for [Doom\_3.html Doom 3]. This will help you understand and write them:

